  "issue_title": "Add a test suite",
  "issue_body": "**Problem**\n\nThe repository ships with zero automated tests. `package.json` has no `test` script, no test runner is configured, and `find . -name \"*.test.ts\"` returns nothing. Regressions in pure helpers (cost math, JSON extraction from LLM output, manifest scope classification, YAML frontmatter parsing) can ship unnoticed.\n\n**Proposal**\n\nAdd Vitest as the test runner and a starter suite covering the project's pure, exported helpers. Keep the first PR narrow:\n\n- No library code changes\n- No filesystem / network / Anthropic SDK mocking\n- No React component tests\n- Just pure functions that are easy to reason about and have clear contracts\n\n**Scope of the initial suite**\n\n| Module | Functions |\n|---|---|\n| `lib/integrations/anthropic.ts` | `calcCost`, `estimateTokensFromText` |\n| `lib/integrations/search.ts` | `extractJson` |\n| `lib/sources.ts` | `classifyScope`, `formatBytes` |\n| `lib/safe-matter.ts` | `parseMarkdown` (happy path + line-by-line fallback) |\n\n**Acceptance criteria**\n\n- [ ] `vitest` added as a devDependency\n- [ ] `vitest.config.ts` resolves the `@/*` alias to match `tsconfig.json`\n- [ ] `npm test` runs the suite once; `npm run test:watch` runs in watch mode\n- [ ] Tests live under `tests/` (mirrors the existing `lib/`, `app/`, `worker/`, `scripts/` layout)\n- [ ] All tests pass locally with `npm test`\n\n**Follow-ups (separate issues / PRs)**\n\n- GitHub Actions CI running `npm test` on push and PR\n- Component / integration tests with filesystem fixtures\n- ESLint configuration\n- Coverage reporting and a coverage gate\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-21T13:44:44.000Z",
  "test_cmd": [
    "npm",
    "test",
    "--",
    "--passWithNoTests"
  ],
